01:26.102 --> 01:30.047
THE SKIN I LIVE IN

02:39.560 --> 02:41.846
Help me with the dumb waiter.

02:45.727 --> 02:47.385
Open it.

02:48.518 --> 02:49.762
Take this.

03:14.685 --> 03:16.427
Marilia, are you there?

03:20.310 --> 03:21.423
Yes.

03:21.602 --> 03:24.469
Send up more cloth
and double-sided tape.

03:25.310 --> 03:27.763
I can't get it until tomorrow.

03:28.393 --> 03:29.969
OK.

03:31.685 --> 03:36.426
I also wanted a needle,
thread and scissors.

03:36.602 --> 03:38.888
You're joking, right?

03:39.810 --> 03:41.516
Yeah.

04:19.685 --> 04:22.007
Our face identifies us.

04:22.142 --> 04:25.509
For burn victims,
saving their lives is not enough.

04:25.602 --> 04:31.101
They need to have a face
even if it's from a corpse.

04:31.477 --> 04:32.471
A face with features...

04:32.560 --> 04:35.309
so they can gesticulate.

04:35.352 --> 04:36.928
I have participated in

04:37.102 --> 04:39.507
three out of the nine
face transplants

04:39.602 --> 04:43.133
carried out in the world...

04:43.227 --> 04:46.674
and they were the most moving
experiences of my life.

04:49.102 --> 04:50.132
Good...

04:50.227 --> 04:52.797
For a shapeless mass to acquire
the features that will give it expression...

04:52.852 --> 04:56.513
we have to mould the muscles...

04:56.602 --> 05:02.716
articulating the facial musculature
with the corresponding nerve endings.

05:02.852 --> 05:04.558
MATERNITY HOSPITAL

08:49.727 --> 08:53.388
Vera, I've brought you some opium.

09:03.893 --> 09:05.386
OPERATING THEATER

09:27.102 --> 09:29.471
Can you breathe more gently?

09:30.143 --> 09:32.548
If you want me
to stop breathing, kill me.

09:32.643 --> 09:34.302
Don't talk rubbish.

09:37.310 --> 09:39.596
How long will all this last?

09:39.810 --> 09:42.477
Your skin is softer than I thought.

09:42.602 --> 09:44.971
If you don't end it, I will.

09:45.060 --> 09:47.346
If you'd wanted to kill yourself...

09:47.435 --> 09:49.591
you'd have tried to cut your jugular.

09:50.143 --> 09:51.766
In any case...

09:53.477 --> 09:56.179
I didn't know your skin was so soft.

10:04.560 --> 10:06.136
Here it is...

10:06.685 --> 10:08.971
taken from the animal
while it was still alive.

10:10.102 --> 10:11.642
Thank you.

13:22.560 --> 13:25.392
Now there won't be any more burns.

13:27.143 --> 13:29.596
You said that a year ago.

13:30.518 --> 13:32.390
I was hasty.

13:39.477 --> 13:41.514
Tell me if it burns you.

13:41.893 --> 13:43.351
No.

13:45.727 --> 13:47.552
And now?

13:47.977 --> 13:49.802
No.

13:51.810 --> 13:53.516
Now!

13:53.643 --> 13:55.184
I have given the name "Gal"...

13:55.310 --> 13:57.596
to the artificial skin
I've been working on...

13:57.685 --> 13:58.715
in recent years.

13:58.810 --> 14:01.512
Tell me if the mosquito bites you.

14:01.643 --> 14:04.890
This skin is resistant
to every insect bite...

14:04.977 --> 14:06.304
No.

14:06.477 --> 14:08.514
...which means a natural barrier to

14:08.643 --> 14:11.973
...malaria, for example.

14:12.268 --> 14:16.132
Naturally, I've carried out
a rigorous quality control...

14:16.477 --> 14:19.095
on the tissues implanted in mammals...

14:19.185 --> 14:20.180
specifically, in athymic mice...

14:20.310 --> 14:22.265
and the results...

14:22.393 --> 14:27.134
...have been spectacular.

14:27.227 --> 14:29.052
This leads me to suppose

14:29.102 --> 14:31.139
they would be equally positive...

14:31.227 --> 14:33.016
in human mammals.

14:34.893 --> 14:38.590
What does the name Gal mean?
Are they initials?

14:38.727 --> 14:40.303
That was my wife's name.

14:40.435 --> 14:42.639
She was burned to death in a car crash.

14:42.810 --> 14:45.559
In you presentation you stated...

14:46.143 --> 14:50.635
that the skin is resistant to insect bites
and could prevent malaria.

14:50.768 --> 14:52.474
What makes you think that?

14:52.852 --> 14:56.098
The artificial skin is much harder
than human skin...

14:56.227 --> 14:57.849
and it smells different.

14:57.977 --> 14:59.599
It's been proven that the malaria mosquito...

14:59.685 --> 15:02.256
distinguishes human skin by the smell.

15:02.435 --> 15:04.923
Gal smells different and repels it.

15:05.060 --> 15:07.015
Let's see if we can get rid of him.

15:07.185 --> 15:08.726
That isn't enough.

15:10.393 --> 15:12.929
How did you toughen the skin?

15:13.435 --> 15:15.011
Excuse me.

15:17.268 --> 15:19.306
Let's go somewhere quieter.

15:19.393 --> 15:21.846
There's only one way to toughen skin.

15:21.935 --> 15:23.724
By mutating it.

15:24.435 --> 15:26.011
Yes, that's what I did.

15:26.102 --> 15:27.760
Transgenesis.

15:28.602 --> 15:32.263
Yes.
I transferred genetic information...

15:33.018 --> 15:35.933
from a pig's cell to a human cell.

15:36.393 --> 15:37.720
A pig's cell?

15:37.810 --> 15:39.599
It's much stronger than ours.

15:39.685 --> 15:41.178
You're insane!

15:41.602 --> 15:44.635
You know the application
of transgenetic therapy...

15:44.768 --> 15:46.309
in humans is completely forbidden!

15:46.435 --> 15:47.513
Yes, I do.

15:47.602 --> 15:51.298
And, forgive me,
but it seems the ultimate paradox.

15:51.935 --> 15:54.470
We intervene in everything around us...

15:54.602 --> 15:57.848
meat, clothes,
vegetables, fruit, everything!

15:57.935 --> 16:01.715
Why not use scientific advances
to improve our species?

16:01.768 --> 16:03.178
You know how many diseases...

16:03.268 --> 16:05.259
we could cure with transgenesis?

16:05.352 --> 16:07.721
Or the genetic malformations
that could be avoided?

16:07.768 --> 16:09.226
Don't go on!

16:09.310 --> 16:11.431
I know the list by heart...

16:11.768 --> 16:14.387
and I think of it every day.

16:15.477 --> 16:16.673
But even so...

16:16.768 --> 16:20.134
I must forbid you from
investigating further...

16:20.268 --> 16:22.259
or I'll be forced to report you...

16:22.310 --> 16:23.933
to the scientific community.

16:24.018 --> 16:25.973
Over and above what you or I may think...

16:26.060 --> 16:30.054
the bioethics are
absolutely clear about this.

16:30.143 --> 16:35.429
Don't worry.
Gal was a personal adventure.

16:35.727 --> 16:38.013
I did it in memory of my wife...

16:38.102 --> 16:40.804
and solely to extend my knowledge.

16:40.893 --> 16:41.841
I remember...

16:41.935 --> 16:44.849
the first time
you told me about this experiment.

16:44.977 --> 16:47.216
It seemed like a dream then.

16:47.643 --> 16:49.136
And it still is.

16:49.268 --> 16:52.634
The president has ordered me
to give it up, indefinitely.

16:52.977 --> 16:55.014
Shit, and it'll be the business
of the century.

16:55.102 --> 16:58.965
It will be,
but we won't benefit from it.

17:01.237 --> 17:03.808
If you give up research,
will you go back to surgery?

17:03.935 --> 17:06.684
Your patients will be delighted.

17:07.227 --> 17:09.383
I don't know.

17:09.518 --> 17:12.551
We've got a waiting list
for operations in "El Cigarral".

17:12.685 --> 17:15.434
- I'm leaving.
- Wait, so am I.

19:09.643 --> 19:12.048
Do you like what you see?

19:13.477 --> 19:15.597
What do you mean?

19:17.685 --> 19:20.304
Is there anything you want to improve?

19:21.602 --> 19:23.142
No.

19:23.477 --> 19:26.095
I don't want to improve anything.

19:27.310 --> 19:30.142
Can I take it I'm finished?

19:31.185 --> 19:32.843
Yes...

19:33.227 --> 19:36.557
and you can boast of having
the best skin in the world.

19:42.810 --> 19:44.884
And now what?

19:45.435 --> 19:48.102
Now I'm going to light
this opium pipe...

19:48.185 --> 19:50.057
and smoke it.

19:50.477 --> 19:52.348
I mean us.

19:53.227 --> 19:54.803
Me.

19:54.893 --> 19:58.010
What are you going to do with me?

19:59.227 --> 20:01.300
I don't know.
I'll think about it.

20:01.393 --> 20:02.507
When?

20:02.602 --> 20:05.137
If you keep on, I'm leaving!

20:05.768 --> 20:08.766
Couldn't we just live?

20:10.352 --> 20:12.389
Live together.

20:12.727 --> 20:14.764
Live together?

20:15.227 --> 20:18.141
- How?
- Like everyone.

20:19.727 --> 20:22.393
You and I aren't like everyone.

20:24.268 --> 20:26.638
Look on it as another
of your experiments.

20:26.685 --> 20:28.094
Living together as equals.

20:28.185 --> 20:31.017
That's it!

20:38.727 --> 20:40.184
Here.

20:40.852 --> 20:43.305
I could set fire
to the house with this.

20:49.560 --> 20:51.266
I'm yours.

20:52.352 --> 20:54.591
I'm made to measure for you.

20:55.227 --> 20:58.011
And you've just told me
that you like me.

20:58.435 --> 21:00.260
Did I say that?

21:02.727 --> 21:05.096
I know you look at me.

21:06.727 --> 21:08.468
Since you brought me here,

21:08.518 --> 21:11.267
we practically live in the same room.

21:17.518 --> 21:19.094
In this pocket.

21:55.393 --> 22:02.511
<i>Carnival celebrations
are being held on the Gran Via.</i>

22:09.185 --> 22:11.720
You shouldn't have used her face.

22:12.060 --> 22:15.307
If I'd been here,
I'd have warned you of the danger.

22:15.643 --> 22:17.930
There's a resemblance,
but she isn't the same.

22:18.018 --> 22:20.092
The resemblance is too strong.

22:20.685 --> 22:22.971
Have you thought
what to do with her?

22:23.102 --> 22:24.381
No.

22:24.518 --> 22:28.678
You'll have to kill her
or keep her hidden here forever.

22:29.977 --> 22:32.761
Why all the hurry to get rid of her?

22:33.060 --> 22:36.093
If you don't kill her,
she'll kill herself.

22:36.435 --> 22:38.591
Stories repeat themselves.

22:39.893 --> 22:41.599
No! Not this one!

22:42.143 --> 22:45.674
Vera is stronger, a born survivor.

22:46.018 --> 22:48.009
You're sick.

22:48.310 --> 22:49.684
If you don't get rid of her...

22:49.768 --> 22:52.932
what you feel now will end up
devouring you, like a cancer.

22:53.685 --> 22:56.387
When you realize, it'll be too late.

22:57.893 --> 23:01.555
How are you so sure of what I feel
if even I don't know?

23:02.977 --> 23:05.891
Because I know you as if I'd borne you.

23:06.102 --> 23:08.768
Fire the servants
and don't hire anyone.

23:45.477 --> 23:47.266
What do you want?

23:47.643 --> 23:51.340
<i>To see my mother.
I haven't seen her for ten years.</i>

23:51.560 --> 23:52.673
If she was a servant...

23:52.727 --> 23:55.096
they've just left and won't be back.

23:56.352 --> 23:59.054
<i>I saw them,
but she wasn't one of them.</i>

23:59.227 --> 24:00.803
<i>My mother is prettier.</i>

24:00.893 --> 24:02.848
Go away or I'll call the police.

24:15.352 --> 24:17.177
Zeca!

24:19.685 --> 24:22.683
I'm your son, Zeca.

24:22.810 --> 24:24.552
How dare you come here!

24:24.685 --> 24:26.094
Open the door!

24:26.185 --> 24:31.933
It's Carnival. We're both far
from Bahia and I'm homesick.

24:32.352 --> 24:36.760
Look! Like the costume I wore
when I was little. Remember?

24:39.935 --> 24:41.641
Little tiger!

24:41.852 --> 24:44.138
I just want to see you for a minute.

24:44.310 --> 24:47.059
Very well, but then you leave.

24:47.477 --> 24:49.053
Whatever you say.

24:49.185 --> 24:53.759
Follow the path and keep going
through the second gate.

25:18.852 --> 25:20.225
How did you find us?

25:20.310 --> 25:24.434
I've been in Spain a while.
I saw Robert in the paper.

25:24.602 --> 25:26.343
He was giving a...

25:28.185 --> 25:29.761
I don't know,
something in Madrid.

25:29.852 --> 25:31.759
I went there
and then followed him here.

25:31.810 --> 25:32.888
Can't I come in?

25:32.935 --> 25:36.265
No, I'm not allowed visitors.

25:36.768 --> 25:39.470
It smells good.
I'm hungry.

25:41.435 --> 25:42.892
Brute!

25:52.268 --> 25:54.223
<i>The main new items today...</i>

25:54.310 --> 25:57.059
<i>are the Carnival celebrations...</i>

25:57.185 --> 26:00.348
<i>and the daring robbery committed
in the Bvlgari jewellery store...</i>

26:00.393 --> 26:02.384
<i>in the heart of Madrid.</i>

26:02.518 --> 26:03.797
<i>It happened last night...</i>

26:03.935 --> 26:06.388
<i>and today we have the first images
recorded by one...</i>

26:06.435 --> 26:12.633
<i>of the twenty-four security cameras
which protect the jewellery store.</i>

26:13.893 --> 26:16.216
<i>Apart from the thief,
who appears in the image...</i>

26:16.268 --> 26:19.799
<i>police are looking
for one of the store's employees...</i>

26:19.893 --> 26:23.887
<i>who has been missing
for the last twenty-four hours.</i>

26:24.352 --> 26:27.266
As if they were going to find him!

26:28.227 --> 26:30.513
The bastard just had to
turn off the cameras...

26:30.602 --> 26:32.924
but he changed his mind
and left one working.

26:33.060 --> 26:35.595
He'll be rotting in hell now.

26:35.768 --> 26:37.558
And the police are looking for you.

26:37.643 --> 26:41.554
Sure. If it weren't Carnival,
I couldn't go out.

26:41.935 --> 26:43.925
You can hide me here for a few days.

26:44.018 --> 26:45.475
Hide you here?

26:45.518 --> 26:46.632
Not a chance.

26:46.893 --> 26:49.595
We've got loads of patients.
A lot of people come here.

26:49.685 --> 26:51.675
I know how to hide.

26:51.810 --> 26:55.341
Anyway, I want Robert
to operate on my face.

26:55.477 --> 26:57.183
Robert?

26:57.227 --> 26:59.300
When he gets you on the table...

26:59.352 --> 27:02.468
he'll give you a lethal injection!

27:02.768 --> 27:05.102
How could you think
he'd operate on you...

27:05.137 --> 27:06.559
after what you did?

27:06.602 --> 27:08.758
I'll have to blackmail him.

27:11.477 --> 27:14.759
If I kidnap you,
could I make him do it?

27:15.685 --> 27:18.173
You're raving mad.

27:18.560 --> 27:21.013
I'm just a servant.

27:21.435 --> 27:24.184
Anyway, Robert's out of Spain.

27:25.518 --> 27:27.094
Even better.

27:27.310 --> 27:29.763
I'll stay here till he comes back.

27:33.643 --> 27:35.017
Where are you going?

27:35.102 --> 27:37.555
- What do you want
- A drink.

27:40.185 --> 27:43.515
Take the bottle,
take what you want, just get out!

28:09.768 --> 28:10.965
What's this?

28:11.102 --> 28:12.642
It's a film!

28:13.018 --> 28:14.511
Go away!

28:38.102 --> 28:41.965
- She reminds me of...
- She doesn't remind you of anybody!

28:42.685 --> 28:44.261
Get out or I'll shoot.

28:45.518 --> 28:46.975
Mom...

28:47.643 --> 28:50.511
you wouldn't do that to your son.

28:51.310 --> 28:55.138
You're not my son.
I just gave birth to you.

28:55.852 --> 28:58.305
- It's her.
- It's not her!

28:58.393 --> 28:59.934
How could it be her?

29:00.352 --> 29:02.010
Get out of here!

29:02.143 --> 29:03.553
Keep away!

29:10.935 --> 29:12.641
Marilia?

29:13.393 --> 29:15.882
I heard a noise, like a shot.

29:16.435 --> 29:17.928
Is anything wrong?

29:18.018 --> 29:19.973
<i>I heard voices too.</i>

29:21.060 --> 29:22.683
<i>Marilia?</i>

29:23.018 --> 29:24.511
Marilia!

29:47.227 --> 29:48.767
There.

31:17.143 --> 31:18.056
Who is it?

31:18.185 --> 31:20.140
It's me, Zeca. Open the door.

31:20.685 --> 31:22.059
I can't.

31:22.185 --> 31:25.099
- Why not?
- I haven't got the key.

31:25.310 --> 31:26.933
Does Marilia have it?

31:27.185 --> 31:29.471
- I don't know.
- What are you doing here?

31:52.310 --> 31:54.715
If you scream, I'll break your jaw.

32:02.935 --> 32:05.139
Where's the key to upstairs?

32:06.143 --> 32:08.264
In the drawer at the corner.

32:08.768 --> 32:10.593
Untie me and I'll give it to you.

32:10.643 --> 32:12.349
No, where is it?

32:13.102 --> 32:16.763
In that drawer, in an envelope.

32:23.227 --> 32:25.513
- It's not here!
- At the back!

32:31.060 --> 32:32.885
There's just an envelope
that says "clips".

32:33.018 --> 32:36.964
- That's to fool people, idiot!
- Look inside.

32:43.018 --> 32:46.964
No. Not the napkin. No, no, no!

32:47.060 --> 32:49.548
- Yes, or else you'll scream.
- No, untie me, please!

32:49.685 --> 32:51.012
Open your mouth!

32:52.685 --> 32:56.631
Open it wider, mom!

32:57.810 --> 33:00.345
It all fit before.

33:46.935 --> 33:48.641
Did Robert send you?

33:49.643 --> 33:50.922
No.

33:51.102 --> 33:54.597
How did you survive?
I left you burning like a torch.

33:58.560 --> 34:01.392
He saved me.

34:02.935 --> 34:05.009
Get me out of here!

34:05.102 --> 34:07.139
I'll go anywhere with you!

34:08.643 --> 34:10.433
You're saying that...

34:10.518 --> 34:12.260
because I'm on top of you.

34:13.143 --> 34:14.469
No!

34:15.101 --> 34:18.716
Ask me for anything!

34:18.768 --> 34:21.766
What can you give me,
apart from a great fuck?

34:21.893 --> 34:24.464
I don't know. Lots of things!

34:24.893 --> 34:26.516
I'll do whatever you want.

34:28.810 --> 34:30.847
You could help me with Robert.

34:30.976 --> 34:32.766
How do you get on with him now?

34:33.685 --> 34:35.225
Great.

34:36.060 --> 34:38.429
- Great?
- Yes.

34:38.893 --> 34:42.259
- And he still locks you in?
- You know what he's like!

34:42.351 --> 34:43.809
Yes.

34:45.643 --> 34:47.882
I'll take you with me.

34:48.018 --> 34:49.973
That might soften his heart
and he'll fix my face.

34:51.060 --> 34:55.433
If you kidnap me,
you can ask him for anything!

34:57.018 --> 34:59.685
I'll kidnap you, but first we'll fuck.

35:04.727 --> 35:05.970
Listen...

35:06.727 --> 35:07.674
What?

35:07.768 --> 35:10.055
Letâ€™s fuck in the garden, please!

35:10.143 --> 35:14.054
The garden? Why?
I'm sick of screwing in the open air.

35:14.352 --> 35:16.223
This tiger wants a bed.

35:22.935 --> 35:24.641
Don't you like it?

35:24.977 --> 35:26.434
You're hurting me.

35:27.143 --> 35:28.684
It's very big.

35:28.810 --> 35:31.559
It's like it always was.
It used to drive you crazy.

35:32.102 --> 35:33.025
Yes...

35:33.060 --> 35:35.727
and it still does.
It drives me crazy!

35:35.977 --> 35:40.550
Shut up! You're weird,
you're distracting me.

36:54.185 --> 36:55.843
Kill her!

36:57.018 --> 36:58.511
Kill them both!

37:28.101 --> 37:31.348
As children,
they played at killing each other.

37:32.560 --> 37:35.925
I knew that one day
they'd do it for real.

37:38.018 --> 37:40.139
The tiger and Robert?

37:40.768 --> 37:42.178
Yes.

37:42.893 --> 37:44.469
They're brothers...

37:45.476 --> 37:47.597
but they don't know it.

37:48.351 --> 37:50.674
At least I've never told them.

37:52.726 --> 37:56.388
I had Zeca by a servant
who disappeared soon after.

37:57.476 --> 38:02.264
And Robert is the son of Mr. Ledgard.

38:02.643 --> 38:07.715
Their fathers were very different
but both were born insane.

38:10.018 --> 38:12.222
It's my fault.

38:18.685 --> 38:21.967
I've got insanity in my entrails.

38:22.518 --> 38:25.185
I'd served at the Ledgards' house
since I was a child.

38:25.310 --> 38:27.596
Mrs. Ledgard was sterile...

38:28.185 --> 38:32.759
and when my Robert was born,
they kept him...

38:34.643 --> 38:37.392
and said she'd given birth to him.

38:39.435 --> 38:43.096
But I was the one who looked after him
from the day he was born.

38:45.226 --> 38:48.094
Zeca spoke to me as if he knew me.

38:48.268 --> 38:52.428
He mistook you for Gal,
Robert's wife.

38:54.476 --> 38:58.221
Unlike Robert,
Zeca grew up far from me.

39:00.518 --> 39:04.180
When he was seven,
he started transporting drugs.

39:04.310 --> 39:08.350
I never saw him.
He grew up on the street.

39:10.768 --> 39:17.973
About twelve years ago
Zeca came back to the house.

